TASK1.2:THE BASIC COMMANDS TO CONFIGERE GIT




 1. CONFIGURE GIT (FIRST TIME SETUP)
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"

 2. VERIFY CONFIGURATION
git config --list

 3. CHECK GIT INSTALLATION
git --version

 4. NAVIGATE TO PROJECT FOLDER
cd XYZ_Project

 5. INITIALIZE GIT REPOSITORY
git init

 6. CREATE .gitignore FILE
touch .gitignore
 (Windows alternative)
echo > .gitignore

 7. ADD SECURITY RULES TO .gitignore
echo .env >> .gitignore
echo .env.local >> .gitignore
echo .env.production >> .gitignore
echo node_modules/ >> .gitignore

 8. CHECK STATUS
git status

 9. ADD ALL FILES TO STAGING AREA
git add .

 10. FIRST COMMIT
git commit -m "Initial project setup with git configuration and gitignore"

 11. CONNECT TO GITHUB REPOSITORY
git remote add origin https://github.com/USERNAME/REPO.git

 12. SET MAIN BRANCH
git branch -M main

 13. PUSH TO GITHUB
git push -u origin main



TASK1.3:USE OF GITHUB REPOSITORY





 1. SET UP PROJECT DIRECTORY
mkdir PersonalFinanceApp
cd PersonalFinanceApp

 2. CONFIGURE GIT (FIRST TIME ONLY)
git config --global user.name "Alex"
git config --global user.email "alex@example.com"

 3. VERIFY GIT INSTALLATION
git --version

 4. CLONE GITHUB REPOSITORY (MAIN STEP)
git clone https://github.com/USERNAME/PersonalFinanceApp.git
cd PersonalFinanceApp

 5. CREATE INITIAL FILES
echo "# Personal Finance App" > README.md
touch .gitignore

 6. ADD .gitignore SECURITY RULES
echo .env >> .gitignore
echo .env.local >> .gitignore
echo node_modules/ >> .gitignore

 7. CHECK STATUS
git status

 8. ADD FILES TO STAGING AREA
git add .

 9. FIRST COMMIT
git commit -m "Initial setup with gitignore"

 10. PUSH TO GITHUB
git push origin main




TASK2.1DD FILE CHANGES TO GIT STAGING AREA




 1. CHECK PROJECT STATUS
git status

:: 2. CREATE OR MODIFY FILES
touch feature.html
 (edit main.html manually)

 3. REVIEW CHANGES IN A FILE
git diff main.html

 4. DELETE UNNECESSARY FILE (if any)
rm unwanted_file.txt
:: OR
git rm unwanted_file.txt

 5. ADD FILE CHANGES TO STAGING AREA

 Add specific file
git add main.html

 Add multiple files
git add main.html feature.html

 Add all changes (recommended)
git add .
6. VERIFY STAGING AREA
git status

 7. COMMIT CHANGES
git commit -m "Added feature.html, updated main.html, removed unwanted file"

 8. PUSH TO GITHUB (if connected)
git push origin main




