TASK 3.1:FETCH FILES FROM GITHUB REPOSITORY.


:: 1. CLONE REMOTE REPOSITORY (Alice)
git clone https://github.com/USERNAME/GBY.git
cd GBY

:: 2. FETCH SPECIFIC BRANCH (Bob – subscribe to updates)
git fetch origin feature-branch
git checkout feature-branch

:: 3. SYNC ALL BRANCHES (Claire – full synchronization)
git fetch --all
git pull --all

:: 4. NORMAL UPDATE (David – standard pull like email sync)
git checkout main
git pull origin main

:: 5. PULL SPECIFIC BRANCH (Emma – targeted download)
git pull origin feature-branch

:: 6. FORCE UPDATE / OVERWRITE LOCAL FILES (Frank)
git fetch origin
git reset --hard origin/main

:: 7. UPDATE TO LATEST STABLE VERSION (Grace)
git checkout main
git pull origin main


TASK 3.2:PUSH FILES TO REMOTE BRANCH.



:: 1. CHECK CURRENT BRANCH
git branch

:: 2. CREATE AND SWITCH TO FEATURE BRANCH
git checkout -b feature-new

:: 3. MAKE CHANGES TO FILES
:: (edit project files)

:: 4. ADD FILES TO STAGING AREA
git add .

:: 5. COMMIT LOCAL CHANGES
git commit -m "Implemented new feature"

:: 6. PUSH LOCAL BRANCH TO REMOTE (ORIGIN MASTER OR FEATURE BRANCH)
git push origin feature-new
:: OR (as required in question)
git push origin master
